closing_comment: Note that the POI you put a note on is a _guidepost_ (i.e. simple pointy signs that give direction to important nearby places):  <https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/5966546840> <https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tag:information%3Dguidepost>  While another POI you mentioned across the road is an information _office_ (i.e. where there are town staffs to answer tourists' questions), and it was marked as such:  <https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/5912053740> <https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tag:information%3Doffice>  Both of them are giving information to travelers <https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tag:tourism%3Dinformation>, though the later is more useful if you are not looking just for simple direction; but they do have a limited service hours, and you would have to knock and ask.  Note that the main OpenStreetMap site displays these differently, as a guidepost icon V.S. a circle-(i) icon:  <https://www.openstreetmap.org/#map=19/13.76675/100.50099>  I also re-verified both POIs yesterday in-person, after I saw your note.  If MAPS.ME still displays these two as a same thing, maybe you should bring the application's developer attention to this problem? So they could fix them:  <https://github.com/mapsme/omim/issues/7845>

opening_comment: Elephant pride sanctuary We are a  sanctuary in Chiang Mai with 5 adults and 1 baby elephant. For us, it is not just about the conservation of elephants, our staff live side by side with them. Elephants have an average life of 60-80 years which is very similar to people, so we wish to provide them a comfortable place to live in nature. Our goal is to allow people to experience the amazing elephants while maintaining the honor and pride of these incredible animals. Our tour consists of walking in the jungle with the elephants, feeding, mud bath, and bathing in a river. Lunch will be provided and there is also drive to a beautiful waterfall .This is a full day tour. Customers will be picked up in the morning from their hotel and driven to the sanctuary in a car with air condition. At the end of the day all customers will be returned to their hotels.
